###
1. Convert Dos TO Unix Using tr Command
$ tr -d '\r' < input.file > output.file

2. Perl One Liner
$ perl -pi -e 's/\r\n/\n/g' input.file

3. Convert DOS newlines (CR/LF) to Unix format using sed command
If you are using BASH shell type the following command
    (press Ctrl-V then Ctrl-M to get pattern or special symbol)
$ sed 's/$//' input.txt > output.txt
3. Convert UNIX to DOS format using sed command
$ sed 's/$'"/`echo \\\r`/" input.txt > output.txt

