### ------------------------------ GIT ---------------------------------------
$ ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "email"

   1. Checkout Windows-style, commit Unix-style (core.autocrlf = true)
   2. Checkout as-is, commit Unix-style (core.autocrlf = input)
   3. Checkout as-is, commit as-is (core.autocrlf = false)

The first option is the default, which I find rather unfortunate—I don’t consider
line ending manipulation to be the responsibility of my VCS. Instead, 
I prefer to keep core.autocrlf set to false 
and let my text editors deal with line endings. 
(If you like having core.autocrlf set to true or input, I’d love to hear why.)

$ git config core.whitespace cr-at-eol

